<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8632> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8632" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 739, footnote 123" ;
	dprr:hasID 8632 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3413> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3413" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elected under Peducaeus' plebiscite as special inquisitor into the case of the accused Vestals (see above, Tribunes of the Plebs, and 114, Vestal Virgins), he condemned and put to death the two who had been acquitted by the Pontifices, and others besides, not without incurring some suspicion of political bias (Ascon. 45-46 C; Cic. ND 3.74; Brut. 160; Liv. Per. 63; Val. Max. 3.7.9; 6.8.1; Plut. RQ 83; Dio 26, fr. 87; Obseq. 37; Porphyr. in Hor. Sat. 1.6.30; Oros. 5.15.22; Macrob. Sat. 1.10.5, from Fenestella; Zon. 7.8; cf. coins of the Cassii, Grueber, CRRBM 1.482; Cesano, Stud. Num. 1 [1942] 219; see Münzer, APF 243-245, and RE s. v. \"Marcia\" no. 114)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3413 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3246> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3246" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 125. They completed the census (Liv. Per. 60) this year, after questioning C. Gracchus for returning from Sardinia before his commander. See Promagistrates." ;
	dprr:hasID 3246 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3237> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3237" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Verr. 2.1.143; Vell. 2.10.1; Frontin. Aq. 1.8; see Degrassi 126, 470f. They brought the Aqua Tepula into Rome (Frontin. Aq. 1.8), and punished Caepio's old enemy, the Augur Lepidus Porcina, for renting a house at 6000 HS (Vell. 2.10.1; Val. Max. 8.1, damn. 7, for building too high a villa at Alsium; cf. Cic. Brut. 97). They named P. Cornelius Lentulus Princeps Senatus (Cic. Div. in Caec. 69; Leg. Agr. 2.82; De Or. 1.211; Brut. 108; Phil. 8.14; Cat. 4.13; Val. Max. 5.3.2; Dio 46.20.5; see 131, Censors)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3237 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3223> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3223" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Chr. 354 (Ravilla et Cinna); Fast. Hyd. (Longino et Cinna); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; and on Cinna, CIL 1\n     .2.654. See Degrassi 126, 470f." ;
	dprr:hasID 3223 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3194> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3194" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The latest possible date for their praetorships under the Lex Villia." ;
	dprr:hasID 3194 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3103> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3103" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Introduced a measure to extend the ballot to all popular trials except those for perduellio (Cic. Brut. 97; 106; Leg. 3.35-37; Sest. 103; Lael. 41; Corn. 1, fr. 50 and Ascon. 78 C; Schol. Bob. 135, and Ps.-Ascon. 216 Stangl; cf. Grueber, CRRBM 1.494f.; Cesano, Stud. Num. 1 [1942] 213f.), which was opposed by Antius and the Consul Lepidus (Cic. Brut. 97)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3103 .
